Dreamweaver

Dreamweaver is a script to install and configure a fresh Debian installation with my daily use desktop.

Usage

1. Clone the repo:

	git clone https://github.com/h3nc4/Dreamweaver.git

2. Run the script:

	Dreamweaver/run

Main Contents

- run: The main script to run. Includes all steps to install and configure your system.
- config/packages.csv: CSV file with the list of packages to be installed.
- config/bash/: My bash configuration files.
- config/profile.d/: Directory with scripts to be sourced by the user profile.
- utils/: Directory with useful scripts to install and configure some applications and tools.

Usage Notes

For optimal security, it is recommended to use this script on an encrypted system, as it includes enabling auto-login and passwordless privileges.

